  "text": "In the hybrid canonical form, the cofactor signature takes precedence over the truth table. It is used to determine the phase and the order of each input variables. Any other signatures that can distinguish input variables, such as the row sums used in [CITATION_1] , can be merged into the canonical form definition. In this paper, only the cofactor signature is used.",
